{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867775295,"sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7be940014YgbiwYOT3aawe","messageID":"msg_d79f7b0f5001uUsk3x1aI5Z0Kg","sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2b5903b4179d4324ac23b664","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n4: - **Language**: Python\n5: - **Size**: L\n6: \n7: ## Directories\n8: \n9: - `notes/` - Meeting notes and research\n10: - `src/` - Source code (not yet created)\n\n(End of file - total 10 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n## Directories\n\n- `notes/` - Meeting notes and research\n- `src/` - Source code (not yet created)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/README.md","time":{"start":1775867775280,"end":1775867775294}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867775299,"sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7c3e4001XUU0HQSSlUS8vs","messageID":"msg_d79f7b0f5001uUsk3x1aI5Z0Kg","sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_472b5759d4074d5ca1e1cca6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI Pack Command\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `pack` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `pack` command validates and prepares agent workspaces, merges CLI overrides into metadata, generates Dockerfiles, and reports paths. This is the first command in the Python CLI toolkit that provides developer-friendly tooling for packaging AI agents for deployment on AgentCube.\n6: \n7: The goal is to:\n8: \n9: 1. **Provide workspace validation** - Ensure agent workspaces have the required structure and files for the target language (Python/Java)\n10: 2. **Enable metadata management** - Load, merge, and persist agent configuration as YAML\n11: 3. **Generate deployment artifacts** - Create Dockerfiles tailored to the agent's language and dependencies\n12: 4. **Support development workflows** - Enable developers to package agents with CLI overrides before building and publishing\n13: \n14: This implementation builds upon the Python SDK design (`python-sdk/design.md`) and CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`).\n15: \n16: ## Scope\n17: \n18: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n19: **Language:** Python  \n20: **Size:** M\n21: \n22: This AR covers:\n23: \n24: - **In scope:**\n25:   - `agentcube` Python package structure under `cmd/cli/`\n26:   - `PackRuntime` class implementation\n27:   - `pack` Typer command with all specified options\n28:   - Metadata validation and merging logic\n29:   - Dockerfile generation for Python and Java agents\n30:   - Workspace structure validation\n31:   - Dependency processing (requirements.txt for Python, pom.xml for Java)\n32:   - Error handling with verbose traceback support\n33:   - Unit tests for pack logic\n34:   - Documentation and usage examples\n35: \n36: - **Out of scope:**\n37:   - `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status` commands (future ARs)\n38:   - Docker SDK integration for actual image building\n39:   - Kubernetes client integration for deployment\n40:   - Cloud provider integrations\n41:   - AgentRuntime CR creation\n42: \n43: ## Current State Analysis\n44: \n45: ### Existing Python SDK\n46: \n47: Per `python-sdk/design.md`, the Python SDK provides:\n48: - `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking deployed agents\n49: - `CodeInterpreterClient` for code execution sessions\n50: - Control plane and data plane HTTP clients\n51: - Exception hierarchy and utilities\n52: \n53: ### CLI Toolkit Specification\n54: \n55: Per `cli-toolkit/spec.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`:\n56: - CLI entry point: `kubectl-agentcube` via Typer\n57: - Package layout: `agentcube/` with `cli/`, `runtime/`, `services/`, `models/` subpackages\n58: - `PackRuntime` class with 17 methods specified\n59: - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 22 fields\n60: - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option parsing\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No Python CLI package** - The `cmd/cli/` directory does not exist\n65: 2. **No PackRuntime implementation** - Only the interface is specified in design docs\n66: 3. **No metadata service** - No implementation for loading/saving `agent_metadata.yaml`\n67: 4. **No Dockerfile generation** - No templates or generation logic exists\n68: 5. **No workspace validation** - No validation logic for Python/Java workspaces\n69: \n70: ## Proposed Changes\n71: \n72: ### 1. Package Structure\n73: \n74: ```\n75: cmd/cli/\n76: ├── pyproject.toml              # Package metadata, dependencies, console script\n77: ├── agentcube/\n78: │   ├── __init__.py             # Version, exports\n79: │   ├── cli/\n80: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Subpackage marker\n81: │   │   └── main.py             # Typer app, pack command, error handling\n82: │   ├── models/\n83: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Models package\n84: │   │   └── pack_models.py      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n85: │   ├── runtime/\n86: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Re-exports runtimes\n87: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py     # PackRuntime class\n88: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py    # Stub for future AR\n89: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py  # Stub for future AR\n90: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n91: │   │   └── status_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n92: │   ├── services/\n93: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Services package\n94: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py # MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n95: │   │   ├── docker_service.py   # DockerService (stub)\n96: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py     # KubernetesProvider (stub)\n97: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # AgentCubeProvider (stub)\n98: │   └── operations/\n99: │       └── __init__.py         # Placeholder\n100: ├── examples/\n101: │   ├── hello-agent/\n102: │   │   └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n103: │   └── math-agent/\n104: │       └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n105: └── tests/\n106:     ├── __init__.py\n107:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py    # PackRuntime unit tests\n108:     ├── test_metadata_service.py # MetadataService tests\n109:     └── fixtures/\n110:         ├── valid_python_agent/     # Valid Python workspace fixture\n111:         └── valid_java_agent/       # Valid Java workspace fixture\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### 2. pyproject.toml\n115: \n116: ```toml\n117: [build-system]\n118: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n119: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n120: \n121: [project]\n122: name = \"agentcube-cli\"\n123: version = \"0.1.0\"\n124: description = \"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\"\n125: readme = \"README.md\"\n126: license = {text = \"Apache-2.0\"}\n127: authors = [\n128:     {name = \"AgentCube Community\", email = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"}\n129: ]\n130: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n131: classifiers = [\n132:     \"Development Status :: 3 - Alpha\",\n133:     \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n134:     \"License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License\",\n135:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n136:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n137:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n138:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n139: ]\n140: \n141: dependencies = [\n142:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n143:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n144:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n145:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n146:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n147:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n148:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n149:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n150:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n151: ]\n152: \n153: [project.optional-dependencies]\n154: k8s = [\n155:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n156: ]\n157: dev = [\n158:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n159:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n160:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n161:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n162:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n163:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n164:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n165: ]\n166: test = [\n167:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n168:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n169:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n170:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n171:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n172: ]\n173: \n174: [project.scripts]\n175: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n176: \n177: [tool.setuptools]\n178: packages = [\"agentcube\", \"agentcube.cli\", \"agentcube.runtime\", \"agentcube.operations\", \"agentcube.services\"]\n179: \n180: [tool.setuptools.package-data]\n181: agentcube = [\"py.typed\"]\n182: \n183: [tool.pytest.ini_options]\n184: asyncio_mode = \"auto\"\n185: testpaths = [\"tests\"]\n186: \n187: [tool.ruff]\n188: line-length = 100\n189: target-version = \"py310\"\n190: \n191: [tool.mypy]\n192: python_version = \"3.10\"\n193: strict = true\n194: warn_return_any = true\n195: warn_unused_ignores = true\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### 3. AgentMetadata Model\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: # agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n202: \"\"\"Agent metadata service and models.\"\"\"\n203: \n204: from __future__ import annotations\n205: \n206: from pathlib import Path\n207: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n208: \n209: import yaml\n210: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n211: \n212: \n213: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n214:     \"\"\"Agent metadata model for agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n215: \n216:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n217:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n218:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n219:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n220:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n221:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n222:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n223:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n224:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n225:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n226:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n227:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n228:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n229:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n230:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n231:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n232:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n233:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n234:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n235:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n236:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n237:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n238: \n239:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n240:     @classmethod\n241:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n242:         if v.lower() not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n243:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n244:         return v.lower()\n245: \n246:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n247:     @classmethod\n248:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n249:         if v.lower() not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n250:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n251:         return v.lower()\n252: \n253:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n254:     @classmethod\n255:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n256:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n257:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n258:         return v\n259: \n260: \n261: class MetadataService:\n262:     \"\"\"Service for loading and saving agent metadata.\"\"\"\n263: \n264:     METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n265: \n266:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n267:         self.verbose = verbose\n268: \n269:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n270:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace directory.\"\"\"\n271:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n272:             metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n273:             if metadata_file.exists():\n274:                 with open(metadata_file, \"r\") as f:\n275:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n276:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n277: \n278:         raise FileNotFoundError(\n279:             f\"No metadata file found. Expected one of: {', '.join(self.METADATA_FILES)}\"\n280:         )\n281: \n282:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n283:         \"\"\"Save metadata to workspace directory.\"\"\"\n284:         metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n285:         with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n286:             yaml.dump(\n287:                 metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n288:                 f,\n289:                 default_flow_style=False,\n290:                 indent=2,\n291:                 sort_keys=False,\n292:             )\n293: \n294:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n295:         \"\"\"Update metadata with provided fields.\"\"\"\n296:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n297:         updated_data = metadata.model_dump()\n298:         updated_data.update(updates)\n299:         updated_metadata = AgentMetadata(**updated_data)\n300:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated_metadata)\n301:         return updated_metadata\n302: \n303:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n304:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\"\"\"\n305:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n306: \n307:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n308:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n309:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n310:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n311: \n312:         return True\n313: \n314:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n315:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n316:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n317:         if not py_files:\n318:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n319: \n320:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n321:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n322:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n323:         if not pom_xml.exists():\n324:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ### 4. MetadataOptions Dataclass\n328: \n329: ```python\n330: # agentcube/models/pack_models.py\n331: \"\"\"Metadata options for CLI option parsing.\"\"\"\n332: \n333: from __future__ import annotations\n334: \n335: from dataclasses import dataclass\n336: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n337: \n338: \n339: @dataclass\n340: class MetadataOptions:\n341:     \"\"\"Options for metadata overrides from CLI.\"\"\"\n342: \n343:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n344:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n345:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n346:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n347:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n348:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n349:     description: Optional[str] = None\n350:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n351:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n352:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n353:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n354:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n355:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n356:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n357:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n358: \n359:     @classmethod\n360:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n361:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n362:         return cls(\n363:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n364:             language=options.get(\"language\"),\n365:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n366:             port=options.get(\"port\"),\n367:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n368:             requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n369:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n370:             workload_manager_url=options.get(\"workload_manager_url\", \"\"),\n371:             router_url=options.get(\"router_url\", \"\"),\n372:             readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\", \"\"),\n373:             readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\", 8080),\n374:             registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\", \"\"),\n375:             registry_username=options.get(\"registry_username\", \"\"),\n376:             registry_password=options.get(\"registry_password\", \"\"),\n377:             agent_endpoint=options.get(\"agent_endpoint\", \"\"),\n378:         )\n379: ```\n380: \n381: ### 5. PackRuntime Implementation\n382: \n383: ```python\n384: # agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py\n385: \"\"\"PackRuntime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n386: \n387: from __future__ import annotations\n388: \n389: import logging\n390: import shutil\n391: from pathlib import Path\n392: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n393: \n394: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n395: from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n396: \n397: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n398: \n399: \n400: class PackRuntime:\n401:     \"\"\"Runtime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n402: \n403:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n404:         self.verbose = verbose\n405:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n406:         if verbose:\n407:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n408: \n409:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n410:         \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n411:         logger.debug(f\"Packing workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n412: \n413:         # Validate workspace structure\n414:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n415: \n416:         # Load or create metadata\n417:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n418: \n419:         # Apply CLI option overrides\n420:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n421: \n422:         # Validate language compatibility\n423:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n424: \n425:         # Process dependencies\n426:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n427: \n428:         # Generate Dockerfile\n429:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n430: \n431:         # Update pack metadata\n432:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n433: \n434:         # Prepare output path\n435:         output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n436: \n437:         logger.info(f\"Successfully packed workspace to: {output_path}\")\n438: \n439:         return {\n440:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n441:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n442:             \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n443:             \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n444:             \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n445:         }\n446: \n447:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n448:         \"\"\"Validate that workspace path exists and is a directory.\"\"\"\n449:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n450:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n451:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n452:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n453: \n454:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n455:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new one.\"\"\"\n456:         try:\n457:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n458:             logger.debug(f\"Loaded existing metadata: {metadata.agent_name}\")\n459:             return metadata\n460:         except FileNotFoundError:\n461:             logger.debug(\"No existing metadata found, creating new one\")\n462:             return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n463: \n464:     def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n465:         \"\"\"Create default metadata for a workspace.\"\"\"\n466:         language = options.get(\"language\", \"python\")\n467:         entrypoint = options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, language)\n468: \n469:         return AgentMetadata(\n470:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n471:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n472:             language=language,\n473:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n474:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n475:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n476:         )\n477: \n478:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n479:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n480:         updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n481: \n482:         for field in [\n483:             \"agent_name\", \"description\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\",\n484:             \"build_mode\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n485:             \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n486:             \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\",\n487:             \"agent_endpoint\",\n488:         ]:\n489:             value = options.get(field)\n490:             if value is not None and value != \"\":\n491:                 updates[field] = value\n492: \n493:         if updates:\n494:             logger.debug(f\"Applying metadata overrides: {updates}\")\n495:             metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n496:             metadata_dict.update(updates)\n497:             metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n498: \n499:         return metadata\n500: \n501:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n502:         \"\"\"Validate language-specific requirements.\"\"\"\n503:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n504:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n505:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n506:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n507: \n508:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n509:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n510:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n511:         if not py_files:\n512:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n513: \n514:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n515:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n516:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n517:         if not pom_xml.exists():\n518:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n519: \n520:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n521:         \"\"\"Process language-specific dependencies.\"\"\"\n522:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n523:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n524:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n525:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n526: \n527:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n528:         \"\"\"Process Python dependencies from requirements.txt.\"\"\"\n529:         requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n530:         if requirements_file.exists():\n531:             logger.debug(f\"Found requirements.txt: {requirements_file}\")\n532:         else:\n533:             logger.debug(\"No requirements.txt found\")\n534: \n535:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n536:         \"\"\"Process Java dependencies from pom.xml.\"\"\"\n537:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n538:         if pom_xml.exists():\n539:             logger.debug(f\"Found pom.xml: {pom_xml}\")\n540:         else:\n541:             logger.debug(\"No pom.xml found\")\n542: \n543:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n544:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for the workspace.\"\"\"\n545:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n546:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n547:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n548:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n549:         else:\n550:             logger.warning(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n551:             return None\n552: \n553:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n554:         with open(dockerfile_path, \"w\") as f:\n555:             f.write(content)\n556: \n557:         logger.info(f\"Generated Dockerfile: {dockerfile_path}\")\n558:         return dockerfile_path\n559: \n560:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n561:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Python agent.\"\"\"\n562:         return f\"\"\"FROM python:3.11-slim\n563: \n564: WORKDIR /app\n565: \n566: # Copy requirements first for better caching\n567: COPY requirements.txt .\n568: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n569: \n570: # Copy application code\n571: COPY . .\n572: \n573: # Expose port\n574: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n575: \n576: # Run the agent\n577: ENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n578: \"\"\"\n579: \n580:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n581:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Java agent.\"\"\"\n582:         return f\"\"\"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n583: \n584: WORKDIR /app\n585: \n586: # Copy pom.xml and download dependencies\n587: COPY pom.xml .\n588: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n589: \n590: # Copy source code and build\n591: COPY src ./src\n592: RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n593: \n594: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n595: \n596: WORKDIR /app\n597: \n598: # Copy built artifact\n599: COPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n600: \n601: # Expose port\n602: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n603: \n604: # Run the agent\n605: ENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n606: \"\"\"\n607: \n608:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n609:         \"\"\"Update metadata after packaging.\"\"\"\n610:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n611:         logger.debug(\"Updated pack metadata\")\n612: \n613:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n614:         \"\"\"Prepare output path for packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n615:         if output_path:\n616:             output = Path(output_path)\n617:             output.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n618:             shutil.copytree(workspace_path, output, dirs_exist_ok=True)\n619:             return output\n620:         return workspace_path\n621: \n622:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n623:         \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace.\"\"\"\n624:         if language == \"python\":\n625:             # Look for main.py or app.py\n626:             for name in [\"main.py\", \"app.py\"]:\n627:                 if (workspace_path / name).exists():\n628:                     return f\"python {name}\"\n629:             # Default to first .py file\n630:             py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n631:             if py_files:\n632:                 return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n633:             return \"python main.py\"\n634:         elif language == \"java\":\n635:             return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n636:         return \"python main.py\"\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ### 6. CLI Main Entry Point\n640: \n641: ```python\n642: # agentcube/cli/main.py\n643: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI main entry point.\"\"\"\n644: \n645: from __future__ import annotations\n646: \n647: import json\n648: import logging\n649: import sys\n650: from pathlib import Path\n651: from typing import List, Optional\n652: \n653: import typer\n654: from rich.console import Console\n655: from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n656: \n657: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n658: \n659: console = Console()\n660: \n661: app = typer.Typer(\n662:     name=\"agentcube\",\n663:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\",\n664:     no_args_is_help=True,\n665:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n666:     add_completion=False,\n667: )\n668: \n669: \n670: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n671:     \"\"\"Version callback.\"\"\"\n672:     if value:\n673:         from agentcube import __version__\n674:         console.print(f\"[bold]AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version:[/bold] {__version__}\")\n675:         raise typer.Exit()\n676: \n677: \n678: @app.callback()\n679: def main(\n680:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n681:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n682:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n683:     ),\n684:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n685: ) -> None:\n686:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n687:     if verbose:\n688:         logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n689: \n690: \n691: @app.command()\n692: def pack(\n693:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n694:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n695:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n696:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n697:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n698:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n699:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n700:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n701:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n702: ) -> None:\n703:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace for deployment.\"\"\"\n704:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n705: \n706:     with Progress(\n707:         SpinnerColumn(),\n708:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n709:         console=console,\n710:     ) as progress:\n711:         progress.add_task(description=\"Packaging workspace...\", total=None)\n712: \n713:         try:\n714:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n715:             result = runtime.pack(\n716:                 workspace_path,\n717:                 agent_name=agent_name,\n718:                 language=language,\n719:                 entrypoint=entrypoint,\n720:                 port=port,\n721:                 build_mode=build_mode,\n722:                 description=description,\n723:                 output=output,\n724:             )\n725: \n726:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Successfully packed agent: [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]\")\n727:             console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n728:             console.print(f\"  Metadata: {result['metadata_path']}\")\n729:             if result.get('dockerfile_path'):\n730:                 console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n731:             if result.get('output_path'):\n732:                 console.print(f\"  Output: {result['output_path']}\")\n733: \n734:         except Exception as e:\n735:             _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n736: \n737: \n738: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n739:     \"\"\"Handle and display errors.\"\"\"\n740:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n741:     if verbose:\n742:         import traceback\n743:         traceback.print_exc()\n744:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n745: \n746: \n747: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n748:     app()\n749: ```\n750: \n751: ### 7. Package Exports\n752: \n753: ```python\n754: # agentcube/__init__.py\n755: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI package.\"\"\"\n756: \n757: __version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n758: __author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n759: __email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n760: \n761: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n762: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n763: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n764: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n765: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n766: \n767: __all__ = [\n768:     \"app\",\n769:     \"PackRuntime\",\n770:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n771:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n772:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n773: ]\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ```python\n777: # agentcube/runtime/__init__.py\n778: \"\"\"Runtime module.\"\"\"\n779: \n780: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n781: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n782: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n783: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n784: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n785: \n786: __all__ = [\n787:     \"PackRuntime\",\n788:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n789:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n790:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n791:     \"StatusRuntime\",\n792: ]\n793: ```\n794: \n795: ### 8. Example Agents\n796: \n797: ```python\n798: # examples/hello-agent/main.py\n799: \"\"\"Hello Agent example.\"\"\"\n800: \n801: from flask import Flask, jsonify\n802: \n803: app = Flask(__name__)\n804: \n805: \n806: @app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\n807: def health():\n808:     return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n809: \n810: \n811: @app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\n812: def invoke():\n813:     return jsonify({\"message\": \"Hello from AgentCube!\"})\n814: \n815: \n816: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n817:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n818: ```\n819: \n820: ```python\n821: # examples/math-agent/main.py\n822: \"\"\"Math Agent example.\"\"\"\n823: \n824: from flask import Flask, jsonify, request\n825: \n826: app = Flask(__name__)\n827: \n828: \n829: @app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\n830: def health():\n831:     return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n832: \n833: \n834: @app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\n835: def invoke():\n836:     data = request.get_json() or {}\n837:     operation = data.get(\"operation\", \"add\")\n838:     a = data.get(\"a\", 0)\n839:     b = data.get(\"b\", 0)\n840: \n841:     if operation == \"add\":\n842:         result = a + b\n843:     elif operation == \"subtract\":\n844:         result = a - b\n845:     elif operation == \"multiply\":\n846:         result = a * b\n847:     elif operation == \"divide\":\n848:         result = a / b if b != 0 else {\"error\": \"Division by zero\"}\n849:     else:\n850:         result = {\"error\": f\"Unknown operation: {operation}\"}\n851: \n852:     return jsonify({\"result\": result})\n853: \n854: \n855: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n856:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n857: ```\n858: \n859: ### 9. Unit Tests\n860: \n861: ```python\n862: # tests/test_pack_runtime.py\n863: \"\"\"Tests for PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n864: \n865: import tempfile\n866: from pathlib import Path\n867: \n868: import pytest\n869: \n870: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n871: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n872: \n873: \n874: @pytest.fixture\n875: def python_workspace():\n876:     \"\"\"Create a temporary Python workspace.\"\"\"\n877:     with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n878:         workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n879:         # Create main.py\n880:         (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\n881: from flask import Flask\n882: app = Flask(__name__)\n883: \n884: @app.route(\"/health\")\n885: def health():\n886:     return {\"status\": \"healthy\"}\n887: \n888: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n889:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n890: \"\"\")\n891:         # Create requirements.txt\n892:         (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"flask>=2.0.0\\n\")\n893:         yield workspace\n894: \n895: \n896: class TestPackRuntime:\n897:     \"\"\"Test PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n898: \n899:     def test_pack_success(self, python_workspace):\n900:         \"\"\"Test successful packaging.\"\"\"\n901:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n902:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n903: \n904:         assert result[\"agent_name\"] == python_workspace.name\n905:         assert result[\"workspace_path\"] == str(python_workspace)\n906:         assert Path(result[\"metadata_path\"]).exists()\n907:         assert Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"]).exists()\n908: \n909:     def test_pack_validate_missing_workspace(self):\n910:         \"\"\"Test validation with missing workspace.\"\"\"\n911:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n912:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"does not exist\"):\n913:             runtime.pack(Path(\"/nonexistent/path\"))\n914: \n915:     def test_pack_validate_no_python_files(self, tmp_path):\n916:         \"\"\"Test validation with no Python files.\"\"\"\n917:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n918:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No Python files found\"):\n919:             runtime.pack(tmp_path)\n920: \n921:     def test_pack_infer_entrypoint(self, python_workspace):\n922:         \"\"\"Test entrypoint inference.\"\"\"\n923:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n924:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n925: \n926:         metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n927:         metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n928:         assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n929: \n930:     def test_pack_override_options(self, python_workspace):\n931:         \"\"\"Test CLI option overrides.\"\"\"\n932:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n933:         result = runtime.pack(\n934:             python_workspace,\n935:             agent_name=\"custom-agent\",\n936:             language=\"python\",\n937:             entrypoint=\"python custom.py\",\n938:             port=9090,\n939:             build_mode=\"cloud\",\n940:         )\n941: \n942:         metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n943:         metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n944:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"custom-agent\"\n945:         assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python custom.py\"\n946:         assert metadata.port == 9090\n947:         assert metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"\n948: \n949:     def test_generate_python_dockerfile(self, python_workspace):\n950:         \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n951:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n952:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n953: \n954:         dockerfile_path = Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"])\n955:         content = dockerfile_path.read_text()\n956: \n957:         assert \"FROM python:3.11-slim\" in content\n958:         assert \"EXPOSE 8080\" in content\n959:         assert \"ENTRYPOINT python main.py\" in content\n960: ```\n961: \n962: ```python\n963: # tests/test_metadata_service.py\n964: \"\"\"Tests for MetadataService.\"\"\"\n965: \n966: import tempfile\n967: from pathlib import Path\n968: \n969: import pytest\n970: import yaml\n971: \n972: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n973: \n974: \n975: class TestMetadataService:\n976:     \"\"\"Test MetadataService.\"\"\"\n977: \n978:     def test_load_metadata_success(self, tmp_path):\n979:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata.\"\"\"\n980:         # Create metadata file\n981:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n982:         metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n983:             \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n984:             \"language\": \"python\",\n985:             \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n986:             \"port\": 8080,\n987:         }))\n988: \n989:         service = MetadataService()\n990:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n991: \n992:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n993:         assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n994: \n995:     def test_load_metadata_fallback(self, tmp_path):\n996:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata with fallback filenames.\"\"\"\n997:         # Create agent.yaml (fallback)\n998:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\"\n999:         metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n1000:             \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n1001:             \"language\": \"python\",\n1002:             \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n1003:             \"port\": 8080,\n1004:         }))\n1005: \n1006:         service = MetadataService()\n1007:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n1008: \n1009:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n1010: \n1011:     def test_load_metadata_not_found(self, tmp_path):\n1012:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata when file doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n1013:         service = MetadataService()\n1014:         with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError):\n1015:             service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n1016: \n1017:     def test_save_metadata(self, tmp_path):\n1018:         \"\"\"Test saving metadata.\"\"\"\n1019:         service = MetadataService()\n1020:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n1021:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n1022:             language=\"python\",\n1023:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1024:             port=8080,\n1025:         )\n1026: \n1027:         service.save_metadata(tmp_path, metadata)\n1028: \n1029:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n1030:         assert metadata_file.exists()\n1031: \n1032:         saved_data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n1033:         assert saved_data[\"agent_name\"] == \"test-agent\"\n1034: \n1035:     def test_validate_language(self):\n1036:         \"\"\"Test language validation.\"\"\"\n1037:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported language\"):\n1038:             AgentMetadata(\n1039:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1040:                 language=\"javascript\",\n1041:                 entrypoint=\"node main.js\",\n1042:             )\n1043: \n1044:     def test_validate_build_mode(self):\n1045:         \"\"\"Test build mode validation.\"\"\"\n1046:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported build mode\"):\n1047:             AgentMetadata(\n1048:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1049:                 language=\"python\",\n1050:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1051:                 build_mode=\"hybrid\",\n1052:             )\n1053: \n1054:     def test_validate_port_range(self):\n1055:         \"\"\"Test port range validation.\"\"\"\n1056:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Port must be between\"):\n1057:             AgentMetadata(\n1058:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1059:                 language=\"python\",\n1060:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1061:                 port=70000,\n1062:             )\n1063: ```\n1064: \n1065: ### 10. Stubs for Future Commands\n1066: \n1067: ```python\n1068: # agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py\n1069: \"\"\"BuildRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1070: \n1071: from __future__ import annotations\n1072: \n1073: import logging\n1074: from pathlib import Path\n1075: from typing import Any, Dict\n1076: \n1077: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1078: \n1079: \n1080: class BuildRuntime:\n1081:     \"\"\"Runtime for building agent images.\"\"\"\n1082: \n1083:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1084:         self.verbose = verbose\n1085:         if verbose:\n1086:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1087: \n1088:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1089:         \"\"\"Build an agent image.\"\"\"\n1090:         raise NotImplementedError(\"build command not yet implemented\")\n1091: ```\n1092: \n1093: ```python\n1094: # agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n1095: \"\"\"PublishRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1096: \n1097: from __future__ import annotations\n1098: \n1099: import logging\n1100: from pathlib import Path\n1101: from typing import Any, Dict\n1102: \n1103: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1104: \n1105: \n1106: class PublishRuntime:\n1107:     \"\"\"Runtime for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n1108: \n1109:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1110:         self.verbose = verbose\n1111:         self.provider = provider\n1112:         if verbose:\n1113:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1114: \n1115:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1116:         \"\"\"Publish an agent.\"\"\"\n1117:         raise NotImplementedError(\"publish command not yet implemented\")\n1118: ```\n1119: \n1120: ```python\n1121: # agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n1122: \"\"\"InvokeRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1123: \n1124: from __future__ import annotations\n1125: \n1126: import logging\n1127: from pathlib import Path\n1128: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1129: \n1130: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1131: \n1132: \n1133: class InvokeRuntime:\n1134:     \"\"\"Runtime for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n1135: \n1136:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1137:         self.verbose = verbose\n1138:         self.provider = provider\n1139:         if verbose:\n1140:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1141: \n1142:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n1143:         \"\"\"Invoke an agent.\"\"\"\n1144:         raise NotImplementedError(\"invoke command not yet implemented\")\n1145: ```\n1146: \n1147: ```python\n1148: # agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n1149: \"\"\"StatusRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1150: \n1151: from __future__ import annotations\n1152: \n1153: import logging\n1154: from pathlib import Path\n1155: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1156: \n1157: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1158: \n1159: \n1160: class StatusRuntime:\n1161:     \"\"\"Runtime for getting agent status.\"\"\"\n1162: \n1163:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1164:         self.verbose = verbose\n1165:         self.provider = provider\n1166:         if verbose:\n1167:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1168: \n1169:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1170:         \"\"\"Get agent status.\"\"\"\n1171:         raise NotImplementedError(\"status command not yet implemented\")\n1172: ```\n1173: \n1174: ```python\n1175: # agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n1176: \"\"\"DockerService stub.\"\"\"\n1177: \n1178: from __future__ import annotations\n1179: \n1180: import logging\n1181: from pathlib import Path\n1182: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1183: \n1184: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1185: \n1186: \n1187: class DockerService:\n1188:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n1189: \n1190:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1191:         self.verbose = verbose\n1192:         if verbose:\n1193:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1194: \n1195:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n1196:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available.\"\"\"\n1197:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n1198: \n1199:     def build_image(\n1200:         self,\n1201:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n1202:         context_path: Path,\n1203:         image_name: str,\n1204:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n1205:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1206:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1207:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n1208:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n1209: ```\n1210: \n1211: ```python\n1212: # agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n1213: \"\"\"KubernetesProvider stub.\"\"\"\n1214: \n1215: from __future__ import annotations\n1216: \n1217: import logging\n1218: from pathlib import Path\n1219: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1220: \n1221: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1222: \n1223: \n1224: class KubernetesProvider:\n1225:     \"\"\"Provider for Kubernetes operations.\"\"\"\n1226: \n1227:     def __init__(\n1228:         self,\n1229:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1230:         verbose: bool = False,\n1231:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1232:     ) -> None:\n1233:         self.namespace = namespace\n1234:         self.verbose = verbose\n1235:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1236:         if verbose:\n1237:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1238: \n1239:     def deploy_agent(\n1240:         self,\n1241:         agent_name: str,\n1242:         image_url: str,\n1243:         port: int,\n1244:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1245:         replicas: int = 1,\n1246:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1247:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1248:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1249:         \"\"\"Deploy an agent to Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n1250:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Kubernetes provider not yet implemented\")\n1251: ```\n1252: \n1253: ```python\n1254: # agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n1255: \"\"\"AgentCubeProvider stub.\"\"\"\n1256: \n1257: from __future__ import annotations\n1258: \n1259: import logging\n1260: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1261: \n1262: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1263: \n1264: \n1265: class AgentCubeProvider:\n1266:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube CR operations.\"\"\"\n1267: \n1268:     def __init__(\n1269:         self,\n1270:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1271:         verbose: bool = False,\n1272:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1273:     ) -> None:\n1274:         self.namespace = namespace\n1275:         self.verbose = verbose\n1276:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1277:         if verbose:\n1278:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1279: \n1280:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n1281:         self,\n1282:         agent_name: str,\n1283:         image_url: str,\n1284:         port: int,\n1285:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1286:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1287:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1288:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1289:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n1290:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1291:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1292:         \"\"\"Deploy an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n1293:         raise NotImplementedError(\"AgentCube provider not yet implemented\")\n1294: ```\n1295: \n1296: ## Impact Analysis\n1297: \n1298: ### Dependencies\n1299: \n1300: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n1301: |---------|---------|---------|\n1302: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich support |\n1303: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Data validation with BaseModel |\n1304: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML parsing and dumping |\n1305: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future commands |\n1306: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n1307: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Terminal formatting |\n1308: | `packaging` | `>=23.0` | Version parsing |\n1309: | `importlib-resources` | `>=6.0.0` | Resource file access |\n1310: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic versioning |\n1311: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Optional K8s client (optional dependency) |\n1312: | `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Testing (dev dependency) |\n1313: | `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n1314: | `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n1315: \n1316: ### Files to Create\n1317: \n1318: ```\n1319: cmd/cli/\n1320: ├── pyproject.toml\n1321: ├── README.md\n1322: ├── agentcube/\n1323: │   ├── __init__.py\n1324: │   ├── cli/\n1325: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1326: │   │   └── main.py\n1327: │   ├── models/\n1328: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1329: │   │   └── pack_models.py\n1330: │   ├── runtime/\n1331: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1332: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n1333: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n1334: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n1335: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n1336: │   │   └── status_runtime.py\n1337: │   ├── services/\n1338: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1339: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n1340: │   │   ├── docker_service.py\n1341: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n1342: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n1343: │   └── operations/\n1344: │       └── __init__.py\n1345: ├── examples/\n1346: │   ├── hello-agent/\n1347: │   │   ├── main.py\n1348: │   │   └── requirements.txt\n1349: │   └── math-agent/\n1350: │       ├── main.py\n1351: │       └── requirements.txt\n1352: └── tests/\n1353:     ├── __init__.py\n1354:     ├── conftest.py\n1355:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n1356:     ├── test_metadata_service.py\n1357:     └── fixtures/\n1358:         ├── __init__.py\n1359:         ├── valid_python_agent/\n1360:         └── valid_java_agent/\n1361: ```\n1362: \n1363: ### Affected Components\n1364: \n1365: 1. **Build System**: Need to add Python package build to CI/CD\n1366: 2. **Distribution**: Package publishable to PyPI\n1367: 3. **Documentation**: CLI usage documentation needed\n1368: 4. **Examples**: Example agents for testing and demonstration\n1369: \n1370: ### Backward Compatibility\n1371: \n1372: - All code is new with no existing API surface\n1373: - Metadata file format follows spec with fallback support\n1374: - CLI options use sensible defaults\n1375: \n1376: ### Risk Assessment\n1377: \n1378: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n1379: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n1380: | Pydantic v2 API changes | Low | Low | Pin version >=2.0.0, follow migration guide |\n1381: | Docker SDK compatibility | Low | Low | Pin version >=6.0.0, test with multiple Docker versions |\n1382: | YAML parsing edge cases | Low | Low | Comprehensive test coverage for metadata loading |\n1383: | Python version compatibility | Low | Medium | Test against Python 3.10, 3.11, 3.12 |\n1384: | Path handling across OS | Medium | Medium | Use pathlib throughout, test on Linux/MacOS |\n1385: \n1386: ## Alternatives Considered\n1387: \n1388: ### Alternative 1: Click CLI Framework\n1389: \n1390: **Approach**: Use Click instead of Typer for CLI implementation\n1391: \n1392: **Pros**:\n1393: - More mature and widely adopted\n1394: - Larger community and ecosystem\n1395: - More flexible for complex CLI structures\n1396: \n1397: **Cons**:\n1398: - More boilerplate code required\n1399: - Less modern API design\n1400: - Rich integration requires additional setup\n1401: \n1402: **Decision**: Typer provides better developer experience with type hints and built-in Rich support.\n1403: \n1404: ### Alternative 2: Single Metadata File Name\n1405: \n1406: **Approach**: Only support `agent_metadata.yaml` without fallbacks\n1407: \n1408: **Pros**:\n1409: - Simpler implementation\n1410: - Clear canonical filename\n1411: - No ambiguity\n1412: \n1413: **Cons**:\n1414: - Breaking change if filename needs to evolve\n1415: - No backward compatibility with existing agents\n1416: - Less flexible for users\n1417: \n1418: **Decision**: Support fallback filenames (`agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) for better compatibility.\n1419: \n1420: ### Alternative 3: No Dockerfile Generation\n1421: \n1422: **Approach**: Require users to provide their own Dockerfile\n1423: \n1424: **Pros**:\n1425: - More flexibility for custom Dockerfiles\n1426: - No opinionated Dockerfile templates\n1427: - Simpler implementation\n1428: \n1429: **Cons**:\n1430: - Higher barrier to entry for users\n1431: - Inconsistent Dockerfile quality\n1432: - More manual work for simple use cases\n1433: \n1434: **Decision**: Generate sensible default Dockerfiles while allowing user overrides.\n1435: \n1436: ## Testing Strategy\n1437: \n1438: ### Unit Tests\n1439: \n1440: 1. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_success**: Successful packaging with Python workspace\n1441: 2. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_missing_workspace**: Validation with missing directory\n1442: 3. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_no_python_files**: Validation with no Python files\n1443: 4. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_infer_entrypoint**: Entrypoint inference from files\n1444: 5. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_override_options**: CLI option overrides\n1445: 6. **TestPackRuntime.test_generate_python_dockerfile**: Dockerfile content verification\n1446: 7. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_success**: Load from primary filename\n1447: 8. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_fallback**: Load from fallback filename\n1448: 9. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_not_found**: FileNotFoundError on missing\n1449: 10. **TestMetadataService.test_save_metadata**: Save and verify content\n1450: 11. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_language**: Language validator\n1451: 12. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_build_mode**: Build mode validator\n1452: 13. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_port_range**: Port range validator\n1453: \n1454: ### Integration Tests\n1455: \n1456: 1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n1457: 2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n1458: 3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n1459: 4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n1460: \n1461: ### Test Fixtures\n1462: \n1463: - `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n1464: - `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n1465: \n1466: ## Acceptance Criteria\n1467: \n1468: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version and exits\n1469: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack` command with all specified options\n1470: - [ ] Workspace validation for Python (requires .py files) and Java (requires pom.xml)\n1471: - [ ] Metadata loading with fallback filenames (`agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`)\n1472: - [ ] Metadata saving to `agent_metadata.yaml` in correct YAML format\n1473: - [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n1474: - [ ] Dockerfile generation for Python agents\n1475: - [ ] Dockerfile generation for Java agents\n1476: - [ ] Entrypoint inference from workspace files\n1477: - [ ] Verbose error handling with traceback\n1478: - [ ] Rich progress spinner during pack operation\n1479: - [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n1480: - [ ] Package installs via `pip install -e .`\n1481: - [ ] Example agents pack successfully\n1482: - [ ] Pydantic validators reject invalid language/build_mode/port values\n1483: \n1484: ## References\n1485: \n1486: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: CLI Toolkit Specification\n1487: - `cli-toolkit/design.md`: CLI Toolkit Design\n1488: - `python-sdk/design.md`: Python SDK Design\n1489: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n1490: - Pydantic v2 Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n1491: - Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 1491 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI Pack Command\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `pack` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `pack` command validates and prepares agent workspaces, merges CLI overrides into metadata, generates Dockerfiles, and reports paths. This is the first command in the Python CLI toolkit that provides developer-friendly tooling for packaging AI agents for deployment on AgentCube.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide workspace validation** - Ensure agent workspaces have the required structure and files for the target language (Python/Java)\n2. **Enable metadata management** - Load, merge, and persist agent configuration as YAML\n3. **Generate deployment artifacts** - Create Dockerfiles tailored to the agent's language and dependencies\n4. **Support development workflows** - Enable developers to package agents with CLI overrides before building and publishing\n\nThis implementation builds upon the Python SDK design (`python-sdk/design.md`) and CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`).\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775867775282,"end":1775867775295}}}}
