{"type":"text","timestamp":1775867779358,"sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7d64d001aZ6zvSLfSECKCk","messageID":"msg_d79f7c977001Z1OllRvA536yev","sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me create the proposal.md for AR-022 (CLI publish command) following the same structure as AR-020:","time":{"start":1775867779357,"end":1775867779357}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868034116,"sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7d91f001wjEJKCclVdVCmW","messageID":"msg_d79f7c977001Z1OllRvA536yev","sessionID":"ses_286087b58ffeW84PjbSXw784EZ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_428eee7c48464727b3c9cd68","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","content":"# AR-022: CLI Publish Command\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `publish` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `publish` command deploys agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform using either the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR). This command completes the agent deployment workflow after `pack` and `build` commands.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Support dual-provider deployment** - Enable deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) or AgentCube platform (AgentRuntime CR) via `--provider` flag\n2. **Handle image preparation** - Prepare container images via local Docker push or accept pre-built image URLs for cloud build mode\n3. **Manage deployment lifecycle** - Create or patch Kubernetes resources, wait for rollout readiness, and report deployment status\n4. **Persist deployment metadata** - Update agent metadata with deployment information including agent_id, endpoint URLs, and session configuration\n\nThis implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and leverages the Kubernetes provider patterns from `deployment/client-go.md`.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `PublishRuntime` class implementation with all specified methods\n  - `publish` Typer command with all specified options (workspace, version, image_url, credentials, provider, node_port, replicas, namespace, etc.)\n  - AgentCube provider integration for AgentRuntime CR deployment\n  - Standard Kubernetes provider integration for Deployment/Service\n  - Image preparation logic for local and cloud build modes\n  - Readiness probe waiting with 120s timeout\n  - Metadata updates for deployment information\n  - Error handling with verbose traceback support\n  - Unit tests for publish logic\n  - Documentation and usage examples\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - `build` command implementation (assumes pre-built image or local Docker availability)\n  - Advanced rollout strategies (canary, blue-green)\n  - Multi-cluster deployment\n  - Custom resource definition management (assumes CRDs already installed)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### AR-020 Pack Command\n\nAR-020 established:\n- `agentcube` Python package structure under `cmd/cli/`\n- `PackRuntime` class with workspace validation and Dockerfile generation\n- `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 22 fields\n- `MetadataService` for loading/saving `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- CLI entry point with Typer framework\n\n### CLI Toolkit Specification\n\nPer `cli-toolkit/spec.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`:\n- `publish` command options: workspace, version, image_url, image_username, image_password, description, region, cloud_provider, provider, node_port, replicas, namespace, verbose\n- Provider options: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n- `PublishRuntime` class with 8 methods specified\n- AgentCube provider prerequisites: requires `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` in metadata\n- Standard K8s publish flow: deploy_agent → wait_for_deployment_ready → update metadata\n\n### Kubernetes Client-Go Patterns\n\nPer `deployment/client-go.md`:\n- CRD API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- CRD plural: `agentruntimes`\n- Typed client interface: `AgentRuntimeInterface` with Create/Update/Get/Delete methods\n- CustomObjectsApi for dynamic CR operations\n\n### Gaps Identified\n\n1. **No PublishRuntime implementation** - Only stub exists from AR-020\n2. **No provider integration** - KubernetesProvider and AgentCubeProvider are stubs\n3. **No image preparation logic** - No Docker push or image URL handling\n4. **No readiness waiting** - No deployment readiness polling\n5. **No AgentRuntime CR schema** - CR structure not fully specified\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. PublishRuntime Implementation\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n\"\"\"PublishRuntime for deploying agents.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\nfrom agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\nfrom agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\nfrom agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for publishing agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish an agent to Kubernetes or AgentCube.\"\"\"\n        logger.debug(f\"Publishing agent from workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n\n        # Load metadata\n        metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n        # Apply CLI overrides\n        self._apply_publish_options(metadata, options)\n\n        # Validate prerequisites\n        self._validate_publish_prerequisites(metadata, options)\n\n        # Prepare image for publishing\n        image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n\n        # Deploy based on provider\n        if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n            agent_info = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url, **options)\n        elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n            agent_info = self._publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url, **options)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported provider: {self.provider}\")\n\n        # Update publish metadata\n        self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n\n        logger.info(f\"Successfully published agent: {metadata.agent_name}\")\n\n        return agent_info\n\n    def _apply_publish_options(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n        updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n\n        for field in [\n            \"version\", \"description\", \"region\", \"registry_url\",\n            \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\",\n        ]:\n            value = options.get(field)\n            if value is not None and value != \"\":\n                updates[field] = value\n\n        # Handle namespace separately (not in AgentMetadata initially)\n        namespace = options.get(\"namespace\")\n        if namespace:\n            updates[\"namespace\"] = namespace\n\n        if updates:\n            logger.debug(f\"Applying publish overrides: {updates}\")\n            metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n            metadata_dict.update(updates)\n            # Note: May need to extend AgentMetadata with namespace field\n\n    def _validate_publish_prerequisites(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate prerequisites for publishing.\"\"\"\n        # Check build mode\n        if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n            # Local mode requires Docker\n            if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n                raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n\n        # AgentCube provider prerequisites\n        if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n            if not metadata.router_url or not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n                raise ValueError(\n                    \"AgentCube provider requires 'router_url' and 'workload_manager_url' \"\n                    \"in agent_metadata.yaml. Please run 'pack' with --router-url and \"\n                    \"--workload-manager-url options.\"\n                )\n\n        # Validate image URL for cloud mode\n        if metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\" and not options.get(\"image_url\"):\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"Cloud build mode requires --image-url to be specified\"\n            )\n\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, image_url: str, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish using AgentCube AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR to Kubernetes\")\n\n        provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n            namespace=options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n            verbose=self.verbose,\n        )\n\n        # Prepare readiness probe\n        readiness_probe_path = metadata.readiness_probe_path or \"/health\"\n        readiness_probe_port = metadata.readiness_probe_port or metadata.port\n\n        # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n        result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n            agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=metadata.port,\n            entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n            env_vars=self._build_agent_env_vars(metadata),\n            workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n            router_url=metadata.router_url,\n            readiness_probe_path=readiness_probe_path,\n            readiness_probe_port=readiness_probe_port,\n        )\n\n        # Wait for deployment readiness\n        provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(metadata.agent_name, timeout=120)\n\n        # Get final status\n        status = provider.get_agent_runtime(metadata.agent_name)\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_name,  # CR name as ID\n            \"deployment_type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"namespace\": options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n            \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"running\") if status else \"unknown\",\n            \"endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\") if status else None,\n            \"router_url\": metadata.router_url,\n            \"workload_manager_url\": metadata.workload_manager_url,\n        }\n\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, image_url: str, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish using standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"Deploying standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service\")\n\n        provider = KubernetesProvider(\n            namespace=options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n            verbose=self.verbose,\n        )\n\n        # Prepare deployment config\n        replicas = options.get(\"replicas\", 1)\n        node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n        env_vars = self._build_agent_env_vars(metadata)\n\n        # Deploy\n        result = provider.deploy_agent(\n            agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=metadata.port,\n            entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n            replicas=replicas,\n            node_port=node_port,\n            env_vars=env_vars,\n        )\n\n        # Wait for deployment readiness\n        provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(metadata.agent_name, timeout=120)\n\n        # Get final status\n        status = provider.get_agent_status(metadata.agent_name)\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"deployment_type\": \"Kubernetes\",\n            \"namespace\": options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n            \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n            \"service_name\": result[\"service_name\"],\n            \"node_port\": result[\"node_port\"],\n            \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n            \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"running\") if status else \"unknown\",\n        }\n\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare container image for publishing.\"\"\"\n        # If image_url is provided, use it directly\n        if options.get(\"image_url\"):\n            logger.info(f\"Using provided image URL: {options['image_url']}\")\n            return options[\"image_url\"]\n\n        # For local build mode, build and push image\n        if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n            return self._prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n        elif metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\":\n            return self._prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare local Docker image.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"Building and pushing local Docker image\")\n\n        # Build image tag\n        tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n        image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:{tag}\"\n\n        # Build Dockerfile path\n        dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Dockerfile not found at {dockerfile_path}\")\n\n        # Build image\n        build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n            dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n            context_path=workspace_path,\n            image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            tag=tag,\n        )\n\n        logger.info(f\"Built image: {image_name} (ID: {build_result['image_id']})\")\n\n        # Push to registry if credentials provided\n        registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n        username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n        password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n\n        if registry_url and username and password:\n            pushed_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n            push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n                image_name=image_name,\n                registry_url=registry_url,\n                username=username,\n                password=password,\n            )\n            logger.info(f\"Pushed image to: {pushed_image}\")\n            return pushed_image\n        else:\n            logger.warning(\"Registry credentials not provided. Image built but not pushed.\")\n            return image_name\n\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare cloud-built image (requires external build service).\"\"\"\n        logger.info(\"Cloud build mode - expecting pre-built image\")\n\n        # In cloud mode, image should be provided or built by external service\n        if not options.get(\"image_url\"):\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"Cloud build mode requires --image-url to specify the pre-built image\"\n            )\n\n        return options[\"image_url\"]\n\n    def _build_agent_env_vars(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Build environment variables for agent deployment.\"\"\"\n        env_vars: Dict[str, str] = {}\n\n        # Add metadata fields as env vars\n        if metadata.workload_manager_url:\n            env_vars[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = metadata.workload_manager_url\n        if metadata.router_url:\n            env_vars[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = metadata.router_url\n        if metadata.agent_endpoint:\n            env_vars[\"AGENT_ENDPOINT\"] = metadata.agent_endpoint\n\n        return env_vars\n\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update metadata after publishing.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n        # Update fields from agent_info\n        updates = {\n            \"agent_id\": agent_info.get(\"agent_id\"),\n            \"agent_endpoint\": agent_info.get(\"endpoint\") or agent_info.get(\"service_url\"),\n            \"image\": {\n                \"url\": agent_info.get(\"image_url\"),\n                \"type\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_type\"),\n            },\n            \"k8s_deployment\": {\n                \"type\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_type\"),\n                \"namespace\": agent_info.get(\"namespace\"),\n                \"name\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_name\") or agent_info.get(\"agent_name\"),\n            },\n        }\n\n        # Merge updates\n        metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n        for key, value in updates.items():\n            if value is not None:\n                metadata_dict[key] = value\n\n        updated_metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n        self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated_metadata)\n        logger.debug(\"Updated publish metadata\")\n```\n\n### 2. AgentCubeProvider Implementation\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n\"\"\"AgentCubeProvider for AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ntry:\n    from kubernetes import client, config\n    from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n    K8S_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    K8S_AVAILABLE = False\n    logger.warning(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n\n\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n\n    API_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    API_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n    CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n\n        if not K8S_AVAILABLE:\n            raise ImportError(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n\n        # Initialize Kubernetes client\n        try:\n            if kubeconfig:\n                config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n            else:\n                config.load_incluster_config()\n        except config.ConfigException:\n            logger.warning(\"Failed to load Kubernetes config, attempting default config\")\n            config.load_kube_config()\n\n        self.api_client = client.ApiClient()\n        self.custom_objects_api = client.CustomObjectsApi(self.api_client)\n\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n        core_v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n        try:\n            core_v1.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n            logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                logger.info(f\"Creating namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n                namespace_obj = client.V1Namespace(\n                    metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n                )\n                core_v1.create_namespace(namespace_obj)\n            else:\n                raise\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR: {agent_name}\")\n\n        # Ensure namespace exists\n        self._ensure_namespace()\n\n        # Sanitize name for Kubernetes\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n        # Build environment variables\n        container_env: List[Dict[str, str]] = []\n\n        # Add required AgentCube env vars\n        if workload_manager_url:\n            container_env.append({\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url})\n        elif \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\" not in (env_vars or {}):\n            # Try from environment\n            import os\n            if os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"):\n                container_env.append({\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")})\n\n        if router_url:\n            container_env.append({\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url})\n        elif \"ROUTER_URL\" not in (env_vars or {}):\n            import os\n            if os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"):\n                container_env.append({\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")})\n\n        # Add user-provided env vars\n        if env_vars:\n            for key, value in env_vars.items():\n                if key not in [\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"ROUTER_URL\"]:\n                    container_env.append({\"name\": key, \"value\": value})\n\n        # Build AgentRuntime CR object\n        cr_object = {\n            \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.API_GROUP}/{self.API_VERSION}\",\n            \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"metadata\": {\n                \"name\": sanitized_name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            },\n            \"spec\": {\n                \"agentName\": agent_name,\n                \"image\": image_url,\n                \"port\": port,\n                \"entrypoint\": entrypoint or f\"python main.py\",\n                \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n                \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n                \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n                \"readinessProbe\": {\n                    \"httpGet\": {\n                        \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n                        \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n                    },\n                    \"initialDelaySeconds\": 5,\n                    \"periodSeconds\": 10,\n                    \"timeoutSeconds\": 5,\n                    \"failureThreshold\": 3,\n                },\n                \"env\": container_env if container_env else None,\n            },\n        }\n\n        # Remove None fields\n        cr_object[\"spec\"] = {k: v for k, v in cr_object[\"spec\"].items() if v is not None}\n        if cr_object[\"spec\"].get(\"env\") is None:\n            del cr_object[\"spec\"][\"env\"]\n\n        # Check if CR already exists\n        try:\n            existing = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n            if existing:\n                logger.info(f\"Updating existing AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n                # Update existing CR\n                cr_object[\"metadata\"][\"resourceVersion\"] = existing.get(\"metadata\", {}).get(\"resourceVersion\", \"\")\n                result = self.custom_objects_api.patch_namespaced_custom_object(\n                    group=self.API_GROUP,\n                    version=self.API_VERSION,\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                    plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n                    name=sanitized_name,\n                    body=cr_object,\n                )\n            else:\n                logger.info(f\"Creating new AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n                result = self.custom_objects_api.create_namespaced_custom_object(\n                    group=self.API_GROUP,\n                    version=self.API_VERSION,\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                    plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n                    body=cr_object,\n                )\n        except ApiException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n        logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime deployed: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n            \"cr_name\": sanitized_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n            \"port\": port,\n        }\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Sanitize name for Kubernetes resource.\"\"\"\n        # Kubernetes names must be lowercase, max 63 chars, alphanumeric + hyphen\n        sanitized = name.lower().replace(\"_\", \"-\").replace(\".\", \"-\")\n        sanitized = \"\".join(c for c in sanitized if c.isalnum() or c == \"-\")\n        # Remove leading/trailing hyphens\n        sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n        # Truncate to 63 chars\n        if len(sanitized) > 63:\n            sanitized = sanitized[:63]\n        return sanitized\n\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"Get an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            result = self.custom_objects_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.API_GROUP,\n                version=self.API_VERSION,\n                namespace=namespace,\n                plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n                name=name,\n            )\n            return result\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                logger.debug(f\"AgentRuntime not found: {name}\")\n                return None\n            raise\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, agent_name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Wait for AgentRuntime to be ready.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(f\"Waiting for AgentRuntime {agent_name} to be ready (timeout: {timeout}s)\")\n\n        start_time = time.time()\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n        while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n            try:\n                cr = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n                if cr:\n                    status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n                    phase = status.get(\"phase\", \"\")\n                    conditions = status.get(\"conditions\", [])\n\n                    # Check for ready condition\n                    for condition in conditions:\n                        if condition.get(\"type\") == \"Ready\" and condition.get(\"status\") == \"True\":\n                            logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} is ready\")\n                            return\n\n                    logger.debug(f\"AgentRuntime status: {phase}\")\n\n            except ApiException as e:\n                logger.warning(f\"Error checking AgentRuntime status: {e}\")\n\n            time.sleep(5)\n\n        raise TimeoutError(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n\n    def get_agent_runtime_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime status.\"\"\"\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n        cr = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n\n        if not cr:\n            return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n\n        status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n        return {\n            \"status\": status.get(\"phase\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n            \"cr_name\": sanitized_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"agent_endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\"),\n            \"conditions\": status.get(\"conditions\", []),\n        }\n\n    def delete_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Delete an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n        logger.info(f\"Deleting AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n        try:\n            self.custom_objects_api.delete_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.API_GROUP,\n                version=self.API_VERSION,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n                name=sanitized_name,\n            )\n            logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n            return {\"status\": \"deleted\", \"agent_name\": agent_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                logger.warning(f\"AgentRuntime not found: {sanitized_name}\")\n                return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n            raise\n```\n\n### 3. KubernetesProvider Implementation\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n\"\"\"KubernetesProvider for standard K8s Deployment/Service operations.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ntry:\n    from kubernetes import client, config\n    from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n    K8S_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    K8S_AVAILABLE = False\n    logger.warning(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n\n\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n\n        if not K8S_AVAILABLE:\n            raise ImportError(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n\n        # Initialize Kubernetes clients\n        try:\n            if kubeconfig:\n                config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n            else:\n                config.load_incluster_config()\n        except config.ConfigException:\n            logger.warning(\"Failed to load Kubernetes config, attempting default config\")\n            config.load_kube_config()\n\n        self.apps_v1 = client.AppsV1Api()\n        self.core_v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            self.core_v1.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n            logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                logger.info(f\"Creating namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n                namespace_obj = client.V1Namespace(\n                    metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n                )\n                self.core_v1.create_namespace(namespace_obj)\n            else:\n                raise\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy a standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(f\"Deploying agent: {agent_name}\")\n\n        # Ensure namespace exists\n        self._ensure_namespace()\n\n        # Sanitize name\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n        # Create deployment\n        deployment_result = self._create_deployment(\n            name=sanitized_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=port,\n            entrypoint=entrypoint,\n            replicas=replicas,\n            env_vars=env_vars,\n        )\n\n        # Create service\n        service_result = self._create_service(\n            name=sanitized_name,\n            port=port,\n            node_port=node_port,\n        )\n\n        logger.info(f\"Agent deployed: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n            \"deployment_name\": deployment_result[\"deployment_name\"],\n            \"service_name\": service_result[\"service_name\"],\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n            \"container_port\": port,\n            \"node_port\": service_result[\"node_port\"],\n            \"service_url\": service_result[\"service_url\"],\n        }\n\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n        logger.debug(f\"Creating deployment: {name}\")\n\n        # Build container env\n        container_env: List[client.V1EnvVar] = []\n        if env_vars:\n            for key, value in env_vars.items():\n                container_env.append(client.V1EnvVar(name=key, value=value))\n\n        # Build container\n        container = client.V1Container(\n            name=name,\n            image=image_url,\n            ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n            env=container_env if container_env else None,\n        )\n\n        # Add entrypoint if provided\n        if entrypoint:\n            # Parse entrypoint command\n            import shlex\n            container.command = shlex.split(entrypoint)\n\n        # Build pod spec\n        pod_spec = client.V1PodSpec(\n            containers=[container],\n        )\n\n        # Build pod template\n        pod_template = client.V1PodTemplateSpec(\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(labels={\"app\": name}),\n            spec=pod_spec,\n        )\n\n        # Build deployment spec\n        deployment_spec = client.V1DeploymentSpec(\n            replicas=replicas,\n            selector=client.V1LabelSelector(match_labels={\"app\": name}),\n            template=pod_template,\n        )\n\n        # Build deployment\n        deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n            api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n            kind=\"Deployment\",\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n            spec=deployment_spec,\n        )\n\n        # Create or update deployment\n        try:\n            existing = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n            if existing:\n                logger.info(f\"Updating existing deployment: {name}\")\n                result = self.apps_v1.patch_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace, deployment)\n            else:\n                logger.info(f\"Creating new deployment: {name}\")\n                result = self.apps_v1.create_namespaced_deployment(self.namespace, deployment)\n        except ApiException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Failed to create deployment: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n        return {\n            \"deployment_name\": name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n        }\n\n    def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create Kubernetes NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n        logger.debug(f\"Creating service: {name}\")\n\n        # Determine service type\n        if node_port:\n            service_type = \"NodePort\"\n        else:\n            # Auto-assign NodePort\n            service_type = \"NodePort\"\n            node_port = None  # Let K8s assign\n\n        # Build service port\n        service_port = client.V1ServicePort(\n            port=port,\n            target_port=port,\n            node_port=node_port,\n        )\n\n        # Build service spec\n        service_spec = client.V1ServiceSpec(\n            type=service_type,\n            selector={\"app\": name},\n            ports=[service_port],\n        )\n\n        # Build service\n        service = client.V1Service(\n            api_version=\"v1\",\n            kind=\"Service\",\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n            spec=service_spec,\n        )\n\n        # Create service\n        try:\n            result = self.core_v1.create_namespaced_service(self.namespace, service)\n            actual_node_port = result.spec.ports[0].node_port\n            logger.info(f\"Service created with NodePort: {actual_node_port}\")\n            return {\n                \"service_name\": name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n                \"node_port\": actual_node_port,\n                \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{actual_node_port}\",\n            }\n        except ApiException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Failed to create service: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Wait for Deployment to be ready.\"\"\"\n        logger.info(f\"Waiting for deployment {name} to be ready (timeout: {timeout}s)\")\n\n        start_time = time.time()\n\n        while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n            try:\n                deployment = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n                status = deployment.status\n\n                # Check readiness\n                ready_replicas = status.ready_replicas or 0\n                desired_replicas = status.replicas or 0\n\n                if ready_replicas == desired_replicas and ready_replicas > 0:\n                    logger.info(f\"Deployment {name} is ready ({ready_replicas}/{desired_replicas})\")\n                    return\n\n                logger.debug(f\"Deployment status: {ready_replicas}/{desired_replicas} ready\")\n\n            except ApiException as e:\n                logger.warning(f\"Error checking deployment status: {e}\")\n\n            time.sleep(5)\n\n        raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get agent deployment status.\"\"\"\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n        try:\n            deployment = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n            service = self.core_v1.read_namespaced_service(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n\n            status = deployment.status\n            ready_replicas = status.ready_replicas or 0\n            desired_replicas = status.replicas or 0\n\n            node_port = service.spec.ports[0].node_port if service.spec.ports else None\n\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"running\" if ready_replicas == desired_replicas else \"pending\",\n                \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n                \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n                \"ready_replicas\": ready_replicas,\n                \"desired_replicas\": desired_replicas,\n                \"node_port\": node_port,\n                \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{node_port}\" if node_port else None,\n            }\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n            raise\n\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Delete agent Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n        sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n        logger.info(f\"Deleting agent: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n        results = {\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n\n        # Delete deployment\n        try:\n            self.apps_v1.delete_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n            logger.info(f\"Deployment deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                raise\n            results[\"deployment_status\"] = \"not_found\"\n\n        # Delete service\n        try:\n            self.core_v1.delete_namespaced_service(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n            logger.info(f\"Service deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                raise\n            results[\"service_status\"] = \"not_found\"\n\n        return results\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Sanitize name for Kubernetes resource.\"\"\"\n        # Kubernetes names must be lowercase, max 63 chars, alphanumeric + hyphen\n        sanitized = name.lower().replace(\"_\", \"-\").replace(\".\", \"-\")\n        sanitized = \"\".join(c for c in sanitized if c.isalnum() or c == \"-\")\n        sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n        if len(sanitized) > 63:\n            sanitized = sanitized[:63]\n        return sanitized\n```\n\n### 4. DockerService Enhancement\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n\"\"\"DockerService for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ntry:\n    import docker\n    from docker.errors import DockerException, APIError\n    DOCKER_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    DOCKER_AVAILABLE = False\n    logger.warning(\"Docker SDK not available. Install with: pip install docker\")\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n\n        if not DOCKER_AVAILABLE:\n            raise ImportError(\"Docker SDK not available. Install with: pip install docker\")\n\n        try:\n            self.client = docker.from_env()\n            if verbose:\n                logger.debug(\"Docker client initialized\")\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n            self.client = None\n\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if Docker is available.\"\"\"\n        if self.client is None:\n            return False\n        try:\n            self.client.ping()\n            return True\n        except DockerException:\n            return False\n\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n        import time\n        start_time = time.time()\n\n        logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n\n        if self.client is None:\n            raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n\n        try:\n            image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n                path=str(context_path),\n                dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n                tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n                buildargs=build_args or {},\n                rm=True,\n                pull=False,\n            )\n\n            build_time = time.time() - start_time\n\n            # Get image info\n            image_info = self.get_image_info(image_name)\n\n            logger.info(f\"Image built successfully: {image_name}:{tag}\")\n\n            return {\n                \"image_name\": image_name,\n                \"tag\": tag,\n                \"image_id\": image.short_id,\n                \"image_size\": image_info.get(\"image_size\", \"unknown\"),\n                \"build_time\": f\"{build_time:.2f}s\",\n            }\n\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker build failed: {e}\")\n            raise\n        except Exception as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Build error: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Get image information.\"\"\"\n        return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n\n    def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Get image details.\"\"\"\n        if self.client is None:\n            raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n\n        try:\n            image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n            attrs = image.attrs\n            return {\n                \"image_name\": image_name,\n                \"image_id\": image.short_id,\n                \"image_size\": self._format_size(attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)),\n                \"created\": attrs.get(\"Created\", \"unknown\"),\n            }\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Failed to get image info: {e}\")\n            return {\"image_name\": image_name, \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Format size in human-readable format.\"\"\"\n        for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n            if size_bytes < 1024:\n                return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} {unit}\"\n            size_bytes /= 1024\n        return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} TB\"\n\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Push image to registry.\"\"\"\n        import time\n        start_time = time.time()\n\n        logger.info(f\"Pushing image {image_name} to {registry_url or 'Docker Hub'}\")\n\n        if self.client is None:\n            raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n\n        # Login if credentials provided\n        if username and password:\n            self._docker_login(registry_url, username, password)\n\n        # Tag image if registry URL provided\n        if registry_url:\n            target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n            logger.info(f\"Tagging image: {target_image}\")\n            self._tag_image(image_name, target_image)\n            push_image_name = target_image\n        else:\n            push_image_name = image_name\n\n        try:\n            # Push image\n            push_logs = self.client.images.push(push_image_name)\n\n            push_time = time.time() - start_time\n\n            logger.info(f\"Image pushed successfully: {push_image_name}\")\n\n            return {\n                \"pushed_image\": push_image_name,\n                \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\",\n                \"logs\": push_logs,\n            }\n\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Push failed: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n    def _docker_login(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Login to Docker registry.\"\"\"\n        if self.client is None:\n            raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n\n        registry_url = registry or \"https://index.docker.io/v1/\"\n        logger.debug(f\"Logging in to registry: {registry_url}\")\n\n        try:\n            self.client.login(\n                username=username,\n                password=password,\n                registry=registry_url,\n            )\n            logger.debug(\"Docker login successful\")\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker login failed: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n    def _tag_image(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Tag image.\"\"\"\n        if self.client is None:\n            raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n\n        try:\n            image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n            image.tag(target_image)\n            logger.debug(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Tag failed: {e}\")\n            raise\n\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Remove Docker image.\"\"\"\n        if self.client is None:\n            logger.warning(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n            return False\n\n        try:\n            self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=True)\n            logger.info(f\"Image removed: {image_name}\")\n            return True\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image: {e}\")\n            return False\n```\n\n### 5. CLI Publish Command\n\n```python\n# agentcube/cli/main.py (add publish command)\n\n@app.command()\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Publish an agent to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform.\"\"\"\n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n\n    with Progress(\n        SpinnerColumn(),\n        TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n        console=console,\n    ) as progress:\n        progress.add_task(description=\"Publishing agent...\", total=None)\n\n        try:\n            runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n            result = runtime.publish(\n                workspace_path,\n                version=version,\n                image_url=image_url,\n                image_username=image_username,\n                image_password=image_password,\n                description=description,\n                region=region,\n                cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n                provider=provider,\n                node_port=node_port,\n                replicas=replicas,\n                namespace=namespace,\n            )\n\n            console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Successfully published agent: [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]\")\n            console.print(f\"  Provider: {result.get('deployment_type', 'unknown')}\")\n            console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result.get('namespace', 'default')}\")\n            console.print(f\"  Image: {result.get('image_url', 'unknown')}\")\n\n            if result.get('deployment_type') == 'AgentRuntime':\n                console.print(f\"  Router URL: {result.get('router_url', 'N/A')}\")\n                console.print(f\"  Workload Manager: {result.get('workload_manager_url', 'N/A')}\")\n                if result.get('endpoint'):\n                    console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['endpoint']}\")\n\n            elif result.get('deployment_type') == 'Kubernetes':\n                console.print(f\"  Deployment: {result.get('deployment_name', 'N/A')}\")\n                console.print(f\"  Service: {result.get('service_name', 'N/A')}\")\n                console.print(f\"  NodePort: {result.get('node_port', 'N/A')}\")\n                console.print(f\"  Service URL: {result.get('service_url', 'N/A')}\")\n                console.print(f\"  Replicas: {result.get('replicas', 1)}\")\n\n            console.print(f\"  Status: {result.get('status', 'unknown')}\")\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n```\n\n### 6. Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_publish_runtime.py\n\"\"\"Tests for PublishRuntime.\"\"\"\n\nimport tempfile\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n\nimport pytest\n\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef packaged_workspace():\n    \"\"\"Create a temporary packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n        workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n        # Create main.py\n        (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\nfrom flask import Flask\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route(\"/health\")\ndef health():\n    return {\"status\": \"healthy\"}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n\"\"\")\n        # Create requirements.txt\n        (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"flask>=2.0.0\\n\")\n        # Create Dockerfile\n        (workspace / \"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"\"\"\nFROM python:3.11-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE 8080\nENTRYPOINT python main.py\n\"\"\")\n        # Create metadata\n        (workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\"\"\"\nagent_name: test-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nrouter_url: http://router.default.svc\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager.default.svc\n\"\"\")\n        yield workspace\n\n\nclass TestPublishRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Test PublishRuntime.\"\"\"\n\n    @patch('agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.DockerService')\n    @patch('agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.AgentCubeProvider')\n    def test_publish_cr_provider(self, mock_cr_provider, mock_docker, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test publish with AgentCube provider.\"\"\"\n        # Mock Docker service\n        mock_docker.return_value.check_docker_available.return_value = True\n\n        # Mock CR provider\n        mock_provider = MagicMock()\n        mock_provider.deploy_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n            \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"cr_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"image_url\": \"test-agent:latest\",\n            \"port\": 8080,\n        }\n        mock_provider.wait_for_deployment_ready.return_value = None\n        mock_provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n            \"status\": {\"phase\": \"Running\", \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://agent:8080\"},\n        }\n        mock_cr_provider.return_value = mock_provider\n\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(provider=\"agentcube\")\n        result = runtime.publish(packaged_workspace)\n\n        assert result[\"agent_name\"] == \"test-agent\"\n        assert result[\"deployment_type\"] == \"AgentRuntime\"\n        mock_provider.deploy_agent_runtime.assert_called_once()\n        mock_provider.wait_for_deployment_ready.assert_called_once()\n\n    @patch('agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.KubernetesProvider')\n    def test_publish_k8s_provider(self, mock_k8s_provider, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test publish with standard Kubernetes provider.\"\"\"\n        # Mock K8s provider\n        mock_provider = MagicMock()\n        mock_provider.deploy_agent.return_value = {\n            \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"deployment_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"service_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"node_port\": 30080,\n            \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n            \"replicas\": 1,\n        }\n        mock_provider.wait_for_deployment_ready.return_value = None\n        mock_provider.get_agent_status.return_value = {\n            \"status\": \"running\",\n            \"ready_replicas\": 1,\n            \"desired_replicas\": 1,\n        }\n        mock_k8s_provider.return_value = mock_provider\n\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(provider=\"k8s\")\n        result = runtime.publish(packaged_workspace)\n\n        assert result[\"agent_name\"] == \"test-agent\"\n        assert result[\"deployment_type\"] == \"Kubernetes\"\n        mock_provider.deploy_agent.assert_called_once()\n        mock_provider.wait_for_deployment_ready.assert_called_once()\n\n    def test_publish_validate_missing_router_url(self, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test validation with missing router_url.\"\"\"\n        # Remove router_url from metadata\n        metadata_file = packaged_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(\"\"\"\nagent_name: test-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager.default.svc\n\"\"\")\n\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(provider=\"agentcube\")\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url.*workload_manager_url\"):\n            runtime.publish(packaged_workspace)\n\n    @patch('agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.DockerService')\n    def test_publish_docker_unavailable(self, mock_docker, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test publish when Docker is unavailable.\"\"\"\n        mock_docker.return_value.check_docker_available.return_value = False\n\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(provider=\"k8s\")\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n            runtime.publish(packaged_workspace)\n\n    def test_publish_node_port_range(self, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test NodePort validation.\"\"\"\n        with patch('agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.KubernetesProvider') as mock_k8s:\n            mock_provider = MagicMock()\n            mock_provider.deploy_agent.return_value = {\n                \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n                \"deployment_name\": \"test-agent\",\n                \"service_name\": \"test-agent\",\n                \"namespace\": \"default\",\n                \"node_port\": 30080,\n                \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n            }\n            mock_provider.wait_for_deployment_ready.return_value = None\n            mock_provider.get_agent_status.return_value = {\"status\": \"running\"}\n            mock_k8s.return_value = mock_provider\n\n            runtime = PublishRuntime(provider=\"k8s\")\n            # Valid NodePort\n            result = runtime.publish(packaged_workspace, node_port=30080)\n            assert result[\"node_port\"] == 30080\n\n            # Invalid NodePort (out of range)\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"30000-32767\"):\n                runtime.publish(packaged_workspace, node_port=20000)\n```\n\n### 7. AgentMetadata Extension\n\nAdd namespace field to `AgentMetadata`:\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/metadata_service.py (update)\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    # ... existing fields ...\n    namespace: Optional[str] = Field(\"default\", description=\"Kubernetes namespace for deployment\")\n    # ... rest of fields ...\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes client for CR and standard K8s operations |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image building and pushing |\n| Existing dependencies from AR-020 | - | Typer, Pydantic, PyYAML, etc. |\n\n### Files to Create/Modify\n\n**Create:**\n```\ncmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\ncmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\ncmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py (enhanced from stub)\ncmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py\n```\n\n**Modify:**\n```\ncmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py (add publish command)\ncmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py (implement from stub)\ncmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py (add namespace field)\ncmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py (export PublishRuntime)\ncmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py (export PublishRuntime)\n```\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Kubernetes Cluster**: Requires AgentRuntime CRD to be installed for `agentcube` provider\n2. **Docker Daemon**: Required for local build mode\n3. **Image Registry**: Required credentials for pushing images\n4. **RBAC**: Service account needs permissions to create/update Deployments, Services, and AgentRuntime CRs\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- No breaking changes to existing `pack` command\n- Metadata file format extended with optional `namespace` field\n- Default provider is `agentcube` for consistency with spec\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Kubernetes API version mismatch | Low | Medium | Pin kubernetes client version, test against K8s 1.25+ |\n| CRD not installed | Medium | High | Provide clear error message with installation instructions |\n| Docker daemon unavailable | Medium | Medium | Check availability early, provide helpful error |\n| Image push failures | Low | Medium | Retry logic, verbose logging for debugging |\n| Deployment timeout | Low | Medium | Configurable timeout, progress logging during wait |\n| NodePort conflicts | Low | Low | Let K8s auto-assign if not specified |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Helm Charts for Deployment\n\n**Approach**: Use Helm charts instead of direct Kubernetes API calls\n\n**Pros**:\n- Better support for complex deployments\n- Built-in rollback capabilities\n- Easier configuration management\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional dependency (Helm binary or Helm Python library)\n- More complex for simple use cases\n- Less control over individual resource creation\n\n**Decision**: Direct Kubernetes API calls provide better control and simpler implementation for this use case.\n\n### Alternative 2: Kubernetes Client with Context Manager\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes config contexts for multi-cluster support\n\n**Pros**:\n- Support for multiple clusters\n- Leverages standard kubeconfig contexts\n\n**Cons**:\n- Added complexity for initial implementation\n- Not required for initial use cases\n\n**Decision**: Can be added as a future enhancement when multi-cluster support is needed.\n\n### Alternative 3: Async Kubernetes Operations\n\n**Approach**: Use async Kubernetes client for non-blocking operations\n\n**Pros**:\n- Better performance for concurrent operations\n- Non-blocking readiness waits\n\n**Cons**:\n- Added complexity\n- Requires async HTTP client (aiohttp, httpx)\n- Kubernetes async client less mature\n\n**Decision**: Synchronous operations are sufficient for CLI use case; users expect blocking behavior.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_cr_provider**: Successful AgentRuntime CR deployment\n2. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_k8s_provider**: Successful standard K8s deployment\n3. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_validate_missing_router_url**: Validation error for missing router_url\n4. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_docker_unavailable**: Docker availability check\n5. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_node_port_range**: NodePort validation\n6. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_with_version**: Version tag in image name\n7. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_with_replicas**: Custom replica count\n8. **TestPublishRuntime.test_publish_with_namespace**: Custom namespace deployment\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **test_publish_hello_agent_cr**: Full publish flow with hello-agent to AgentRuntime\n2. **test_publish_hello_agent_k8s**: Full publish flow with hello-agent to standard K8s\n3. **test_publish_with_custom_node_port**: Deploy with specific NodePort\n4. **test_publish_readiness_timeout**: Test deployment timeout behavior\n5. **test_publish_update_existing**: Update existing deployment\n\n### Test Prerequisites\n\n- Kubernetes cluster (kind, minikube, or real cluster)\n- AgentRuntime CRD installed (for CR tests)\n- Docker daemon running (for local build tests)\n- Test image registry or mock registry\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube publish` command with all specified options\n- [ ] AgentCube provider creates/updates AgentRuntime CR\n- [ ] Standard Kubernetes provider creates/updates Deployment and Service\n- [ ] Image preparation for local build mode (build and push)\n- [ ] Image preparation for cloud build mode (use provided image URL)\n- [ ] Readiness waiting with 120s timeout and progress logging\n- [ ] NodePort validation (30000-32767 range)\n- [ ] Replica count support (default: 1)\n- [ ] Namespace support (default: \"default\")\n- [ ] Metadata update after successful publish\n- [ ] Error handling for missing router_url/workload_manager_url (AgentCube provider)\n- [ ] Error handling for Docker unavailability (local build mode)\n- [ ] Verbose error handling with traceback\n- [ ] Rich progress spinner during publish operation\n- [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass against test Kubernetes cluster\n- [ ] Clear error messages for common failure scenarios\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: CLI Toolkit Specification\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md`: CLI Toolkit Design\n- `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes client-go patterns\n- `deployment/spec.md`: Deployment specification\n- Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n- Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n- AgentRuntime CRD API: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775868034098,"end":1775868034111}}}}
